	(203,'Trish','McDermott','tmcdermottpr@aol.com',NULL,NULL,'2012-05-21 05:35:23','5793973a6b0ceeda88c6aae9ead30f7e',NULL,1,0,NULL,'',NULL,1,'Trish McDermott is an accomplished brand story teller and an experienced pokesperson and public relations executive, with strong leadership skills, world-wide press experience, persuasive interpersonal talents, and two Internet startups with acquisition outcomes. \n\nMcDermott was a member of Match.com\'s startup team and helped design and launch the site in 1995. In her ten years serving as Match.com\'s Spokesperson and Vice President of Public Relations, McDermott played a key role in developing the Match.com brand globally. McDermott helped see Match through two acquisitions, and ultimately to the global leadership position it holds today.\n\nIn 2004 McDermott left Match to help launch Engage.com, an early social dating community where friends helped each other find love. Engage was acquired by Spark Networks in 2009.\n\nMcDermott has been featured as a spokesperson on: 60 Minutes, 48 Hours, Nightline, VH1, The Today Show and CNN, and interviewed by: Time, Newsweek, US News and World Reports, American Demographics, Business 2.0, People, US Weekly, Glamour, Cosmo, The Wall Street Journal, The New York Times and The London Financial Times. \n\nMcDermott has lectured at San Francisco\'s Commonwealth Club and D.C.\'s National Press Club. She has written dating and relationship content for Match.com, MSN.com, Lifetimetv.com, Engage.com, Princesscruises.com and TeeBeeDee.com, and has been a frequent guest on radio programs around the world. McDermott appeared as talent in Match.com radio commercials and on the Romance television channel for Princess Cruises.\n',NULL,NULL,0,1,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL),
