	(521,'Mitch','Schultz','themitchschultz@gmail.com',NULL,NULL,'2012-05-24 23:45:38','881d9b7d9cdfb33a98c67b1d1ff40f78','https://s3.amazonaws.com/cf_stage/user/profile/521.jpg?606160',1,3025769,NULL,'',NULL,1,'Mitch Schultz began his life journey in Memphis, Tennessee and has since called Texas,\r\nMinnesota, Colorado, New York, Europe, and Peru home. Guided by his lifelong love of\r\nstorytelling, Mitch has cultivated a multi-disciplinary expertise in transmedia and culture\r\nhacking through writing, directing, and producing.\r\n\r\nHe earned his Bachelor of Science from the University of Texas at Austin, primarily\r\nfocused on media production, communication theory, and information mapping. Soon\r\nafter, Mitch completed his Masters of Fine Arts at New York University’s Tisch School\r\nof the Arts. As researcher at the Interactive Telecommunications Program at Tisch,\r\nhe delved into a curriculum that “explores the imaginative use of communications\r\ntechnologies – how they might augment, improve, and bring delight and art into people’s\r\nlives.” Mitch continues to foster his growth within the academic community by speaking\r\nat universities, conferences, and workshops internationally.\r\n\r\nSchultz has also worked as a branding consultant for VisionLab, a progressive HD cable\r\nchannel dedicated to experimental video art. After the successful launch of VisionLab,\r\nhe shifted into independent film production as Director of Development for Ghost Robot,\r\nconceptualizing media, art, and interactive experiences. Constantly probing the elusive\r\nedge of the human-technology relationship, Mitch co-created the I/O Port installation for\r\nNYC’s JFK International Airport and contributed to R&D for Microsoft’s Amnesia Moon, an\r\nepisodic, interactive sci-fi mystery.\r\n\r\nAs a marketing consultant and commercial producer, Mitch honed his branding skills with\r\nglobal clients in the mainstream, and the underground. He segued from the commercial\r\nrealm into developing Spectral Alchemy, a hybrid entity consisting of a “ponder farm,\r\ntransmedia experiences and culture shape shifter;” or ‘bona fide mythology through the\r\nexploration and formulation of revolutionary edicts via an esoteric modus operandi.’\r\n\r\nFollowing Schultz’s 2011 award winning documentary, DMT: The Spirit Molecule, he\r\nrecently launched the DMTRMX project, a multi-platform experience that serves as the\r\nmodel for the four-part MNTTKA Manifesto. Building from The Spirit Molecule’s new\r\nparadigm for consciousness, the remaining three explore our relationship to the physical/\r\nnatural world, the celebration of that relationship, and the development of a novel\r\nlanguage system to remix a modern mythology.\r\n\r\nMitch also has several fiction collaborations in development, including Douglas Rushkoff’s\r\nEcstasy Club, Guy Garcia’s Skin Deep, and the filmic adaptation of Joe Loya’s lauded\r\nautobiography, The Man Who Outgrew His Prison Cell.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL),
