	(908,'Christopher','Ambler','chris@ambler.net','Insider House, Founder',NULL,'2012-05-29 18:09:47','3ae63a47beab93aa39415d07e44379ed','https://s3.amazonaws.com/cf_stage/user/profile/908.jpg?762718',1,3042801,NULL,'',NULL,1,'I began programming computers in 1979 at the age of 12 when I walked into a store that sold the original Commodore PET and have never looked back. It is both my hobby as well as my career. In the 80\'s, I participated in the development of many of the major commercial BBS packages by helping connect them to what would become the Internet. In the 90\'s, I was the author of the most-used PC version of UUCP (now thankfully obsolete).\n\nI have worked as a developer for Microsoft and seen my share of startups from the inside, both successful and not.\n\nAs the Internet has evolved, I have been involved in just about every aspect of its use and development, from protocols to web-based systems and even the political process, having participated in the formation and operation of ICANN since 1995.\n\nI am equally comfortable with policy, strategy, design and development across all disciplines of computer technology. I have and still do serve in roles ranging from individual contributor through development management and executive-level technology management.\n\nIf a language is used to program a computer, I either already know it or can start using it in a matter of days. I am not married to any particular methodology or model; though I do have my preferences, I am a strong believer in using the right tool for the right job.\nSpecialties\n\nSoftware design, strategy and development, from start to finish.',NULL,NULL,0,15,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2014-04-20 20:51:16','2014-04-20 20:51:51',NULL,NULL,NULL),
