	(959,'Gustavo','De Medeiros','g.medeiros@nationphone.com',NULL,NULL,'2012-05-29 18:59:02','e9a8047f09c841c7cfefa67027202d95','https://s3.amazonaws.com/cf_stage/user/profile/959.jpg?1338317969',1,0,NULL,'',NULL,1,'Gustavo Neiva de Medeiros, Chief Executive Officer\r\nBefore founding NationPhone, Gustavo founded, grew and sold Uniwear, an apparel company he launched during college. In Silicon Valley, he worked as a consultant and entrepreneur for Rotary Rocket, a space launch startup; Veridicom, a biometric startup and vTraction, a former Rabobank venture capital company. Gustavo was a participant in the ITU Rapporteur\'s Group on Implementation of IP telephony in developing countries. Gustavo has a Bachelors and Masters in International Business Studies from Maastricht University (The Netherlands); his thesis examines industry entry strategies. Gustavo also studied at the Harvard Business School and conducted innovation management research at Stanford University\'s Aeronautics Department, where he served as CFO and project leader. Gustavo gives back to the community by serving as an adjunct professor of entrepreneurial finance at Pace University where he teaches MBA students. Gustavo is fluent in Dutch, English, and Portuguese and speaks Spanish, French and German.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL),
	(960,'David','Saintloth','davidsainloth@gmail.com',NULL,NULL,'2012-05-29 18:59:32','1934bb8b9d8ecac6b031bbf002f3eb2f','https://s3.amazonaws.com/cf_stage/user/profile/960.jpg?134283',1,0,NULL,'',NULL,1,'I am a Software Engineer by occupation with a degree in Electrical Engineering from The City College of NY. I self studied illustration as a teen and graphic design in the early days of the internet, the artistic ways of looking at the world help inform my engineering solutions greatly. In 2002, I founded Apriority LLC in order to solve a big problem I identified with how software was developed when I was working at TheStreet.com. \r\n\r\nI felt a social and highly public framework for all human and system actions would be best for ensuring efficient development. This idea became the basis of the Action Oriented Workflow paradigm that I invented and integrated into the platform I was building called AgilEntity. AOW, is a new way of looking at work in a business context, it atomizes the invariant activities involved in management of all business objects and surfaces the actions performed for analysis. \r\n\r\nAt the end of 2011 I extended AOW to include an \"implicit\" workflow capability that applied a statistical learning algorithm to eliminate the need for constructing formal workflows between workers in AgilEntity. Thus, businesses that use this workflow can socially create, dispatch and execute work without knowledge of the agents delegated the work, the implicit workflow algorithm (ADA) does all the \"work\". This technology is the basis of the WorkNetz startup that is the focus of this crowd funding profile.\r\n\r\nWorkNetz will for the first time enable any business to run hyper efficiently by emancipating its existing workforce to enable them to work more creatively but also to enable those workers to maximize their inherent value landscapes by working across all the things they can do. This is a required revolution in how we work that will benefit the businesses by allowing them to drastically reduces costs for creating new goods and services and it will allow the workers to work on their own time and be judged only for the work that they elect to do. As the world continues to automate various industries creating displaced worker pools, WorkNetz uses cutting edge statistical learning to apply automation to solve the problem.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','0000-00-00 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL),
