	(993,'John','Graham','john@buzzboxx.com','buzz boxx entertainment, Founder | Head of Ideas + Creativity',NULL,'2012-05-29 20:10:39','4b5f62d023bcfc773968a2d1e80d0a14','https://s3.amazonaws.com/cf_stage/user/profile/993.jpg?273594',1,2922110,NULL,'',NULL,1,'So how do I best describe myself? I possess \"new school\" ideas with an \"old school\" work ethic and live by the Golden Rule both professionally and personally. I find it odd to refer to myself in the third person so please don\'t expect \"Mr. Graham this or that\" coming from me. I\'m as grounded and straightforward as they come. (Thank you Mom and Dad.)\n\nI was born with a true, \"Think Different\" right and left brain mind usually years ahead of any curve. I “see” things. It has been a blessing and a curse as I\'ve met very few people over the years who have a more active, creative mind who can connect all the dots too. Put a blank page in front of me and I see thousands of possibilities.\n\nI\'ve led big brands agency-side – DeVry, Sony, M&M Mars, McDonald\'s Kids – in advertising and marketing, experiential, trend influence, promotions, shopper marketing, event marketing, entertainment + nightlife marketing, senior marketing, teen marketing, family marketing, you name it. And my teams – emphasis on \"team\" – have won a variety of International and National awards across the disciplines too. \n\nI\'ve been in the startup world since 1992 with the Billboard team producing the Billboard Music Awards on FOX. I’ve been in “tech” since 1994 bootstrapping my own company, buzz boxx – ideas + products from the street, a “crowdsourcing” business that was years ahead of its time.\n\nI genuinely enjoy working with people and get energy from others who are also constantly curious and all about possibilities. I cherish working with true \"rock stars\" and always eager to mentor and coach along the way. \n\nMy career goal – to be the best that I can be and do what I can to help make the world a better place!\n\np.s. Somehow the A.D.D. and 140-character genes have skipped me in today\'s business world. I find attending to details and being thorough from the onset saves much more time. I relate and respect Steve Jobs as the devil is always in the details but first you gotta have a brilliant idea.',NULL,NULL,0,0,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00','2014-04-02 04:33:59',NULL,NULL,NULL),
